x4freetext: Detailed
descriptions of the irradiation channels and the
characteristic data of the reactor as well as neutron
spectrum  parameters (thermal to epithermal flux
ration and the epithermal flux shape factor)
determined by the "Cd-ratio for multi-monitor method".
Miniature neutron source reactor.
Irradiation was performed with and without a
one mm thick Cd box in an outer irradiation channel
at a thermal power level of 15.5 kW, which
corresponds to a thermal neutron flux value of
5.0x10**11 n/cm**2/s preset on the control console
Target materials of low and medium mass nuclei were
made up of high-purity foils and metallic oxides.
Induced radioactivity in detector foils were
counted on a HPGe coaxial detector (ORTEC), which has
a relative efficiency of 10% and resolution of 1.95
keV, at 1.33 MeV, Co-60.
Cadmium ratio method
Data taken from the table 2 in the reference
Approved by S.A. Jonah, 27 January 2011
